<h2>Service injection</h2>

<h4>Injection with global options.</h4>
<CodeSnippet>
    @(@"builder.Services
       .AddScoped&lt;IMessageService, MessageService>()")
</CodeSnippet>

<h4>Injection with global options.</h4>
<CodeSnippet>
    @(@"builder.Services
       .AddScoped<IMessageService>(builder => new MessageService(builder.GetRequiredService<NavigationManager>(), new MessageBarGlobalOptions()
       {
           ShowDismiss = true,
           ClearAfterNavigation = false,
           MaxMessageCount= 5,
           NewestOnTop = true,
       }));")
</CodeSnippet>

<h4>Display the list of messages</h4>
You can display the list of messages using the component <b>FluentMessageBarContainer</b>.
<CodeSnippet>
    @(@"<FluentMessageBarContainer Category=""MESSAGE_CATEGORY"" Format=""MessageFormat.Notification"" />")
</CodeSnippet>

